					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">SMB and Final Fantasy are on opposite ends of the spectrum.  SMB lives and breates in NMI (the only piece of code that doesn't run in NMI is the reset code, which is very short), while Final Fantasy's NMI routine exits immediately and lets the main program resume execution.</div>

					
